Netdata will assume it is a relative number if it is smaller than the duration of the round robin database for this chart. Netdata will adapt this parameter to the boundaries of the round robin database. <-> netdata::::netdata-swagger.yaml::::paths::::/data::::get::::parameters::::parameters_3::::description::::This parameter can either be an absolute timestamp specifying the ending point of the data to be returned, or a relative number of seconds, to the last collected timestamp. Netdata will assume it is a relative number if it is smaller than the duration of the round robin database for this chart. So, if the round robin database is 3600 seconds, any value from -3600 to 3600 will trigger relative arithmetics. Netdata will adapt this parameter to the boundaries of the round robin database.
